data.content:
**In .NET 11, all your sync Cosmos DB calls will throw at runtime — the opt-in is gone.**

EF Core 11 fully removed sync I/O for the Cosmos DB provider. In EF Core 10 you could opt back in, but in 11 there is **no workaround** — `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, and `SaveChanges()` always throw.

**Fix:** Convert everything to async:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

You'll also need to propagate `async`/`await` up through every caller of these methods. Remove any `EnableSyncOverAsync` or similar opt-in configuration — it has no effect in EF Core 11.
